headline: Generative AI, psychiatry and the risks of self-service therapy
description: Millions of people use chatbots like ChatGPT to share their distress, and the scientific community has warned about the risks vulnerable people face. Generative AI has shaken up psychiatric consultations, fueled tech giants' ambitions and emerged as a credible tool for analyzing pathologies.

headline: US military to limit support for allies and prioritize homeland
Defiant protests over US immigration crackdown, child's detention
Macron should not target the European Central Bank
description: The French president has criticized the European Central Bank for keeping interest rates too high. While this criticism holds some truth for France, it does not apply to the rest of the eurozone, and overlooks the fact that France can only secure funding thanks to the strength of the central bank.

headline: How researchers got AI to quote copyrighted books word for word
description: American researchers have found that artificial intelligence systems can memorize entire passages from texts that were, in theory, only intended to train them. This discovery could influence future court cases.

headline: Two previously unknown scores by Johann Sebastian Bach identified after a 35-year investigation
description: Germany has celebrated this revelation, attributed to Peter Wollny, who conducted extensive research after discovering the pieces as a student of musicology.

headline: A stenciled hand, the oldest known prehistoric cave painting, discovered in Indonesia
description: This 'negative hand,' which researchers have dated to at least 67,800 years ago, is now the oldest known example of cave painting. The discovery fills a crucial gap in tracing the path of our species' journey to Australia via Indonesia.

The RN's unspoken attraction to MAGA – and gradual ideological alignment
description: Like other European nationalists, Marine Le Pen has been put in a tough spot by Donald Trump's imperialist offensive. But the MAGA ideological campaign in Europe, of which France is a key target, has won over her Rassemblement National party over the past year.

headline: 'As it ceases to inspire, the US is losing part of itself'
description: Donald Trump's second term has turned the United States into a threat to which the rest of the world has no choice but to adapt. Yet, over the past eight decades, habits and practices have taken root that will be used to counter this new imperialism, writes Le Monde columnist Gilles Paris.

headline: How surveillance companies track smartphone users through advertising data
description: Companies are offering law enforcement agencies the ability to track smartphone users through advertising data gathered on their devices. Le Monde attended confidential presentations of these new surveillance tools to learn more.
